# Hello World Node.js Application

This is a simple "Hello World" Node.js application using Express.js.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js installed on your local machine
- Docker installed on your local machine (optional, for running the application in a container)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/hello-world-nodejs.git
    ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:

    ```bash
    cd hello-world-nodejs
    ```

3. Install dependencies:

    ```bash
    npm install
    ```

### Running the Application

- To run the application locally:

    ```bash
    npm start
    ```

- To run the application in a Docker container:

    ```bash
    docker build -t hello-world-nodejs .
    docker run -p 3000:3000 hello-world-nodejs
    ```

### Usage

- Open your web browser and go to [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to see the "Hello World" message.

### Deployment

This application can be deployed to AWS ECS/Fargate using Terraform. Refer to the Terraform configurations in the `terraform/` directory.

## Contributing

Contributions are welcome! Please feel free to submit a pull request or open an issue if you encounter any problems or have suggestions for improvements.

